article.headline: Stetson 85, Lipscomb 67
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- E.J. Gordon scored 23 points to lead Stetson to an 85-67 victory over Lipscomb on Monday night. Anthony Register had 20 points on 6-of-7 shooting from the field, including 3-for-3 from 3-point range, for the Hatters (6-17, 5-9 Atlantic Sun), while Gabe McMillen added 12 points and six assists and reserve Garfield Blair had 10 points. Eddie Ard had 25 points on 10-of-13 shooting for the Bison (14-8, 10-4), while Brian Fisk added 19 points and Cameron Robinson had 10. Stetson broke from a 47-all tie with a 13-2 run. Gordon, who had eight rebounds and five assists, scored six points in the spurt. The Hatters maintained their double-digit lead in the final minutes as Kris Thomas connected on three 3-pointers in a span of 1:35. Stetson shot 61 percent from the field (31-of-50), including going 9-of-12 on 3-pointers.
